statement.tex:
%text
Examine the continuity of $f(x)$ where
$f(x)$ is defined as 

%
\qquad f(x) = \begin{cases}
			   \sin x - \cos x, x\neq 0 \\
			   -1, x = 0 
			\end{cases}

		\\ \text{What are we being asked in the question?}\\ \text{Is the following assertion correct?}\\ \text{Is the following analysis correct?}

reason.tex:
\text{In Step 2, we proved that f(x) is continuous for}\\
						x\neq 0.\text{ And here, as }\lim_{x\to 0^-}f(x)=\lim_{x\to 0^+}f(x) = f(0),\\
						f(x)\text{ is also continuous at }x=0\implies\text{ continuity everywhere.}
